## Timeline

| # | Time | Transcript | Intent | Pattern | Key Params |
|---|------|-----------|--------|---------|------------|
| 1 | 0.0-X.Xs | "First spoken phrase from your transcript here" | hook | `<pattern-id-from-archetype>` | param1=value, param2=value |
| 2 | X.X-Y.Ys | "Second beat" | section-header | `<pattern-id>` | structural_text="...", emphasis_text="..." |
| 3 | Y.Y-Z.Zs | "Third beat" | concept-demo | `<pattern-id>` | ... |
| ... | | | | | |
| N | A.A-B.Bs | "CTA closer" | cta | `<cta-pattern-id>` | verb_text="comment", keyword_text="..." |

**Intent values** (from each archetype's pattern library):
- `hook` - opening 1-3s, sets the topic via object metaphor or headline card
- `list-preview` - "here are the X things" upfront preview
- `section-header` - marks the start of a new section (header pair, masthead, etc.)
- `tool-reveal` - introduces a specific named product / app / surface
- `concept-demo` - shows what a tool DOES (UI mock, dashboard, flowchart)
- `claim` - speaker delivers a quotable sentence or hero pull-quote
- `proof` - data, screenshot, social-proof slab
- `transition` - bridges between two sections
- `cta` - the engagement instruction at the end (comment X, sign up, etc.)
- `closer` - final hold beat, often a callback to the hook
- `caption-only` - default fallback when no other pattern matches

